Class ConstructedObjectInput<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.forms.inputs.BaseInput<V>
      • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.forms.inputs.AbstractInput<java.lang.String>
        • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.forms.inputs.ConstructedObjectInput<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Input<java.lang.String>, ItemInput<java.lang.String,T>, ListInput<java.lang.String,T>, SuggestedItemInput<java.lang.String,T>

    public class ConstructedObjectInput<T>
extends AbstractInput<java.lang.String>
implements ListInput<java.lang.String,T>
    Input to select a objects dynamically constructed from the configuration service This defaults to the set of class. definitions AppContext.makeObject(Class, String) The target object is further constrained to be assignable to a specific type. For security reasons its important that this class cannot be forced to generate a class other than than those specified.
